{"lemma":"عِقْدَيْ","slug":"عِقْدَيْ","root":"ع.ق.د","root_slug":"ع-ق-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عِقْد","root":"عقد","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":33},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n29876","n29877","n29878","n29879"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%82%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tie, knit, make a knot"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to conclude a bargain or contract"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to build access (to a bridge)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to place (the crown on one's head)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make (لِ (li) someone) a leader"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to warrant"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set (one's heart) upon"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to form seed pods"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make an arch or vault"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to count"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be gathered","examples":[{"text":"عُقِدَ ٱلاِجْتِمَاعُ.","english":"The meeting was held."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to speak with an impediment"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be on the point of forming (of a seed pod)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thicken, get consistent","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hang together (of dogs)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to connect, tie together with a knot"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to complicate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to arch, to vault"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thicken, make consistent (by boiling, etc.)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَقَدَ (ʕaqada, “to tie”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tying together, binding"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tie, bond"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compact, contract, covenant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"connection, cohesion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"decade"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alloy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seed pod"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"denary number"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"making of magic knots"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vault, arch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opinion, belief"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَقِدَ (ʕaqida) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"necklace"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.qa.da/","/ʕa.qi.da/","/ʕaq.qa.da/","/ʕaqd/","/ʕa.qad/","/ʕiqd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29876","headword_ar":"عَقْدٌ","root":"Eqd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.: see 1. ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxo*apN","text_ar":"اُخْذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is syn. with the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^oxiy*N","text_ar":"تَاْخِيذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  As a simple subst.,] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqodapN","text_ar":"عُقْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", third sentence. ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A contract, a compact, a covenant, an agreement, a league, a treaty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an engagement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwdN","text_ar":"عُقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, L.) Agreeably with this explanation, the pl. is used in the Kur v. 1, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Contracts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: or it there means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory statutes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordinances, of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Zj, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenants imposed by God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those imposed mutually by men agreeably with the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2106},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"requirements of religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqidu","text_ar":"مَعَاقِدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwdN","text_ar":"عُقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqidu","text_ar":"مَعَاقِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them are contracts, compacts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A.) ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Responsibility, accountableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suretiship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DamaAnN","text_ar":"ضَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Arafeh, O, K.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoquwdN","text_ar":"مَعْقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arch;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vault;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a structure that is curved in like manner as are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in many instances"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doorways:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * O, L, * K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwdN","text_ar":"عُقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْقَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.]. (L.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAdu Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"اَعْقَادُ السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The arches of the clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqodN","text_ar":"عَقْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b8-  Applied to a he-camel, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the back firmly compacted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaraA","text_ar":"القَرَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoquwdapu","text_ar":"مَعْقُودَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a she-camel. (S, A, O.) ―         -b9-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A decimal number;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of those numbers of which the first is ten and the last is ninety: (I have not found any satisfactory authority for the orthography of the word in this sense; and have therefore followed the general usage, in mentioning it as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqodN","text_ar":"عَقْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the MA, it is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqodN","text_ar":"عِقْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as from only one MS.; and Freytag has mentioned its pl. under"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqodN","text_ar":"عِقْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which I hold to be wrong:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwdN","text_ar":"عُقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the A and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$r","text_ar":"عشر"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$arapu","text_ar":"العَشَرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the first of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euquwd","text_ar":"عُقُود"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","O","L","K","A","S"]},{"entry_id":"n29877","headword_ar":"عِقْدٌ","root":"Eqd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A necklace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a string upon which beads are strung:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwdN","text_ar":"عُقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, L, Msb, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEoqaAdN","text_ar":"مِعْقَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a string upon which beads are strung and which is hung upon the neck of a boy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K;) as does"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqodN","text_ar":"عِقْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqodapN","text_ar":"عُقْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", likewise, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of necklace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["L","TA","O","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n29878","headword_ar":"عَقَدٌ","root":"Eqd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.: see 1, last four sentences. ―         -b2-  Also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A twisting in the tail"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sheep or goat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though it were knotted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied in a knot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A twisting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a knottiness, in the horn"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a hegoat. (L.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A canker, corrosion, rottenness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdiHN","text_ar":"قَادِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) in teeth. (L.) ―         -b4-  See also the next paragraph.       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqadaAnN","text_ar":"عَقَدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29879","headword_ar":"عَقِدٌ","root":"Eqd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqadu","text_ar":"اَعْقَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also, applied to moist earth ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varFY","text_ar":"ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Contracted, and compacted in lumps:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said to be] in this sense a possessive epithet [as distinguished from a part. n.: but see 1, last sentence]. (L.) ―         -b3-  And [as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates, i. e. used as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sand accumulated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"congested;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqadN","text_ar":"عَقَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, L, K;) the latter accord. to AA: (S, O:) n. un. of each with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْقَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiSN","text_ar":"عَقِصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoDapN EaqidapN","text_ar":"رَوْضَةٌ عَقِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A meadow of which the herbage is continuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterrupted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqidN","text_ar":"عَقِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Short, and patient in endurance of labour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K:) or, so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of tree, the leaves of which consolidate wounds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","L","K","IAar"]}]}}